
USAGE:

$f90compiler = Name of your FORTRAN 90 compiler (ifort : Strongly Recommended)

INSTALLATION:

./install $f90compiler

RUN:

./CompPlot -inp  [PDB_filename]
./CompPlot -inp  [PDB_filename] -tar [residue_number-residue_identity]
./CompPlot -inp  2HAQ.pdb
./CompPlot -inp  2HAQ.pdb -tar 151-PHE
./CompPlot -help (for help)

./refresh (To remove intermediate files for an interrupted or pre-terminated run of CompPlot) 
./clean (to reset to the RAW / NASCENT form of the Package) 
If Cleaned, then ensure to run install.csh prior to the next run of CompPlot (see USAGE above)
If only refreshed, no need to re-install the program


